A search has been launched for a man who allegedly sexually assaulted a woman at Leeds train station. CCTV images have now been released in connection with the incident. British Transport Police say the man had got off a train before approaching a young woman waiting on the platform. He began asking her inappropriate questions, before subjecting her to a prolonged sexual assault. The woman moved away from the man and he walked around the station before boarding a train towards Edinburgh. Officers believe the man in the CCTV images may have information which could help their investigation. If you recognise him, or have any information, please contact BTP by texting 61016 or calling 0800 40 50 40 quoting reference 642 of 12/01/23.Alternatively, you can call Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.